data.value: Open Data : Data available for download and usage. (green)   Norway Digital Restricted : Data available only to participants in Norways digital collaboration (yellow). Restricted data : Data not available for download (red).

data.name: Helptext_BoundingBox
data.value: Enter coordinate values for extent, or use pre-defined range names in the drop down list if the geographical data is valid for a specific county or a municipality. You can also enter the coordinates by using the "Select in map" button to define a rectangle in Norgeskart.

data.name: Helptext_ContactMetadata
data.value: Contact point (person or department) that maintains metadata and which can answer questions related to these. "Name" may refer to departmental name or personal name but is not required. Organization name should be written with the name of the organization referred to as external without references to the department. Email should go to public address like drift@etat.no

data.name: Helptext_ContactOwner
data.value: Contact point (person or department) who has an ownership of the data and can answer in depth about the academic issues surrounding the structure and content of the dataset. "Name" may refer to departmental name or personal name but is not required. Organization name should be written with the name of the organization referred to as external without references to the department. Email should go to public address like drift@etat.no

data.name: Helptext_ContactPublisher
data.value: Contact point (person or department) who has an ownership of the data and can answer in depth about the academic issues surrounding the structure and content of the dataset. "Name" may refer to departmental name or personal name but is not required. Organization name should be written with the name of the organization referred to as external without references to the department. Email should go to public address like drift@etat.no

data.name: Helptext_DistributionsFormats
data.value: Multiple formats can be specified. Version of the format provided through files or services, such as gml 3.2.1.

data.name: Helptext_DistributionsFormatsDistributionName
data.value: Only filled in for services and only if the metadata apply to a single layer or group layer in the service and not the entire service.

data.name: Helptext_DistributionsFormatsProtocol
data.value: Select the appropriate distribution form for the resource (data set / service / web page)

data.name: Helptext_DistributionsFormatsURL
data.value: Enter address for download page / webpage or service. For services, URL must be provided with link to GetCapabilities (service and request to be filled out).

data.name: Helptext_Image
data.value: Here you need to upload a large image. Automatically creates a thumbnail image.

data.name: Helptext_KeywordsInspire
data.value: If the dataset contains data contained in the Inspire data sets, it should be referred to GEMET - Inspire themes, version 1.0 and the appropriate theme. There is no requirement that the data set is complete according to an Inspire data set specification. (Own Code List).

data.name: Helptext_KeywordsNationalInitiative
data.value: Keyword list that refers to laws or rules The dataset/series is subject to or binding cooperation to which the data set/series is included. (Own Code List)

data.name: Helptext_KeywordsNationalTheme
data.value: A Norwegian topic category based on the categories from the public map.

data.name: Helptext_KeywordsOther
data.value: This keyword type should preferably not be used, but keywords that are not specified belong to a specific keyword category. It is recommended that keywords be removed from this category and entered under the correct category.

data.name: Helptext_KeywordsPlace
data.value: For example, it may be the municipal name for municipal data sets, or Norways mainland for nationwide data sets. Write places the data set covers instead of what it does not cover.

data.name: Helptext_KeywordsTheme
data.value: Good keywords are a prerequisite for the metadata to be found by the users. Keywords should be written in singular and popular terms should be used in addition to more specific vocabulary. Both overall metadata and more detailed metadata, all the way down to the object level, should be considered.

data.name: Helptext_LicenseTypes

data.name: Helptext_OrderingInstructions
data.value: For services in scope of Norway digital agreement, service declaration in accordance with the terms and conditions of the agreement shall be stated.

data.name: Helptext_ProcessHistory
data.value: Data manufacturers general knowledge of the origin and the process steps of a dataset or service. Explain briefly what weighted operations have been done from data capture to delivery and how this may affect quality and content in the data set

data.name: Helptext_ResolutionScale
data.value: Scale must be entered as an integer (ex: 5000)

data.name: Helptext_SecurityConstraintsNote
data.value: Basis of access restrictions or usage restrictions in the form of legal relationships or other limiting factors. Here you can refer to law, regulation or the like.

data.name: Helptext_Status

data.name: Helptext_TopicCategory

data.name: Helptext_UseConstraints

data.name: Helptext_UseLimitations
data.value: Specifies which areas the data is not suitable for. For example, "the data is not suitable for the municipal area planning" or "can not be used to navigate". One should also state why there are limitations on use.

data.name: HelpTextAbstract
data.value: Enter what the service/dataset contains. What does the user find in this service/dataset.

data.name: HelpTextHelpUrl
data.value: Enter link to external page or PDF document with information and guidance that makes it easier to use the data set.

data.name: HelpTextPurpose
data.value: Specify if the dataset is collected for a particular purpose. If the data can not be used for other purposes without further notice, this should appear here. There is no need to enter anything here whose purpose is not defined. Reference may be made to laws and regulations, parliamentary reports and other disclosures describing the purpose of the data.

data.name: HelpTextResourceReferenceCode
data.value: Full name of the data set itself.

data.name: HelpTextResourceReferenceCodespace
data.value: Final clarification on the naming of namespaces is not available. It is considered to be a URL pointing to a common namespace for geographic data sets managed by the National Geodata Coordinator.

data.name: HelpTextSpesificUsage
data.value: Specify what tasks the data set may/should be used for. For DOK data, particular reference should be made to applications related to the municipalitys planning and construction work. Please state the level of data the data is appropriate for information on whether they are for detailed planning or planning at the overview level. Usage restrictions are filled in on the tab Restrictions

data.name: HelpTextTitle
data.value: Name of metadata entry. The name should be short and consistent and describe the service / dataset as best as possible. General terms must be included in a professional context. The name should be identical to that used in any product specification. The name can also contain year and geographical area.

data.name: HelpTextDate
data.value: The dates refer to the data set or service itself, not metadata. At least one of the fields must be filled out. It is recommended as a minimum that "Date of last revision" is used. If the data is updated continuously, it keeps setting the date of establishment of data set/service ("Date of creation") or first publication of Data Set/Service ("Date of publication"). Time period ("Starting date" and "End date") data set is valid in is not mandatory if date is filled in in at least one of the other fields.

data.name: HelpTextMaintenanceFrequency
data.value: Specifying intervals for modification and other changes to data after they are established.
